DATA CLOUD
Unify Source Profiles

Use identity resolution to consolidate data from different sources into comprehensive views of your customer and accounts. Identity resolution uses matching and reconciliation rules to link data about people or accounts into unified profiles. Each unified profile contains all the unique contact point values from all sources.

Set up identity resolution rulesets after mapping source data to data model objects (DMOs). Mapping must be completed before creating rulesets.

Rulesets

Identity resolution rulesets contain match and reconciliation rules that specify how to link multiple sources of data into a unified profile. Match rules specify how to compare field values to identify matching records. Reconciliation rules specify how to select values from among multiple data sources to retain for each field.

Ruleset Job

The ruleset job processes source profiles according to the map, match, and reconciliation rules you configure to create and update your unified profiles. The job runs at least one time a day for each ruleset, unless it detects no changes in source data or ruleset configuration. If nothing has changed, the ruleset job is skipped.

Unified Profile Objects

Identity resolution consolidates all field values multiple data sources info unified profiles that can be used in processes such as segmentation and activation, calculated insights, reporting, and more. Unification is determined based on the data mappings you create and on match and reconciliation rules specified in the ruleset.

When a ruleset is based on the Individual DMO, information such as first name and last name from multiple data sources is consolidated into unified individual objects. When a ruleset is based on the Account DMO, information such as business name, location, and type is consolidated into unified account objects.

Person accounts can’t be used in identity resolution because they contain a mixture of account and contact fields that don't correspond to either business accounts or individuals.

Unified Contact Point Objects

An individual or account can have multiple valid contact points that should be preserved for each unified individual or unified account. For example, an individual might have both a home phone number and a mobile phone number. Data Cloud creates unified contact point objects to aggregate contact points from different data sources, based on mappings and rules in each ruleset. Unified contact point objects retain all unique contact points for a unified profile.

Unified Link Objects

Unified link objects serve as the link between the source data and unified objects. Unified link objects allow you to view source data of each unified profile and are required for creating calculated insights for unified profiles.

Data Modeling Requirements for Identity Resolution
Data must be mapped correctly in order for identity resolution to process it into unified profiles. Review data modeling requirements to ensure that individual, account, and contact point data is ready for unification.
Identity Resolution Rulesets
Rulesets contain match and reconciliation rules that tell the customer data platform how to link multiple sources of data into a unified profile. Unified profile information is stored in data model objects created by the ruleset.
